picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606231321) stable; urgency=medium

  * Removed the drill-down view's "live"/connection status indicator
    entirely (the small dot + text in the right panel).
  * Fixed a real bug on the camera grid: each tile's status dot was
    ALWAYS gray, regardless of whether the Pi was actually reachable.
    setTileDot() looked up the dot element via getElementById(id)
    using an id constructed from the Pi's name — but buildTile() runs
    to completion (including that lookup) BEFORE the tile is ever
    appended to the document by loadCameraGrid(), so the element
    didn't exist in the DOM yet and the lookup silently returned null
    every time. The dot's color literally never changed, in either
    direction — there was no working green state and no red state at
    all (a red/offline state had never existed in the CSS either).
  * Fixed by holding a direct reference to the dot element inside
    buildTile() and updating it via that reference instead of a DOM
    lookup, removing the ordering dependency entirely. Added an
    .offline class (reusing the existing --danger color already used
    elsewhere in the UI) for the red state, alongside the existing
    .live class for green.
  * Verified against a real running backend with one reachable and
    one unreachable Pi configured side by side: replayed the exact
    fixed logic in Node against the live chain and confirmed the
    working Pi resolves to the live/green class and the broken Pi
    resolves to the offline/red class — not just that the code
    compiles, but that the actual classification is correct.

