picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606231250) stable; urgency=low

  * Switching cameras (Lens) now shows the loading overlay over the
    video and grays out every interactive drill-down control (Stream,
    Lens, Annotate, both Overlay toggles) until the switch is actually
    confirmed — not just sent. Previously only the Lens buttons
    themselves were disabled, and there was no visual feedback on the
    video at all.
  * The confirmation signal is telemetry.active_camera from
    /status.json actually matching the requested camera id — polled
    on a short 300ms interval, separate from the regular slower
    background status poll, with a 10s timeout. This is deliberately
    NOT "first frame arrived" (a frame can arrive before picam-raw's
    sensor switch has actually settled) and NOT a fixed delay.
  * Added a .stream-btn:disabled CSS rule — buttons previously had no
    visual change when .disabled was set via JS, only the toggle
    switches did. Verified the rule applies cleanly alongside .active
    (no overlapping CSS properties between the two, so a switching-
    but-still-selected button correctly shows both its accent tint
    AND a dimmed/disabled appearance at once).
  * Verified end-to-end against a fake picam-raw that simulates a
    realistic ~1.5s camera-switch delay before active_camera updates:
    confirmed the polling logic correctly waits for the real
    confirmation (1823ms measured) rather than resolving immediately
    on the switch command's own response, and confirmed the timeout
    path correctly resolves after the deadline rather than hanging.

