picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606231244) stable; urgency=medium

  * Fixed: fullscreen did not work on iOS. iOS Safari's
    requestFullscreen()/webkitRequestFullscreen() only work on
    <video> elements — calling them on any other element (including
    the .viewer div this app uses, since MJPEG renders as an <img>,
    not a <video>) silently does nothing. There is no iOS-specific
    workaround for the native API on non-video elements.
  * Replaced the native Fullscreen API entirely with a CSS-only
    pseudo-fullscreen: a JS-toggled class that uses position: fixed
    to fill the viewport. One code path on every platform — no
    feature detection, no per-browser branching — so it now behaves
    identically on iOS, Android, and desktop browsers alike, rather
    than depending on an API with inconsistent support.
  * Added an Escape-key handler to exit, since the native API
    provided that automatically and this approach has to wire it up
    manually. Exiting the drill-down view (back to the camera grid)
    while pseudo-fullscreen was active is also now handled — it no
    longer leaves the page scroll-locked.
  * Verified the new markup/JS are present in the actual served page,
    confirmed function hoisting makes showGrid's cleanup call to
    setPseudoFullscreen safe despite the call appearing before the
    function's definition in source order, and confirmed no leftover
    native-Fullscreen-API code remains (only explanatory comments
    referencing why it isn't used).

