picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606230748) stable; urgency=medium

  * Major UI redesign: replaced the always-visible per-Pi sidebar list
    with a single top-level "Cameras" nav item. Clicking it shows a
    grid of thumbnail tiles, one per configured Pi.
  * Each tile proactively checks that Pi's /status.json BEFORE
    attempting any thumbnail stream. Reachable Pis show a live Lores
    MJPEG thumbnail (low bandwidth, appropriate for a grid that may
    have many tiles open at once); unreachable Pis show a "Not
    available" icon instead of a broken-image flash.
  * Clicking a tile drills down into that camera's full view. The
    sidebar Pi list, Stream selector, Lens (camera 0/1), and Annotate
    toggle that used to live in the left sidebar have moved into a
    single bottom bar under the video. Stream info (date/time/lux/
    camera) and the Overlay (OSD) toggles have moved to a right-hand
    panel. A back button returns to the grid.
  * Security hardening found while rebuilding: the tile footer used
    to build HTML via string concatenation with the Pi's configured
    label inserted directly into innerHTML — switched to DOM methods
    (textContent) instead, removing any HTML-injection risk from a
    config value. Pi names are also now sanitized before being used
    as HTML element ids (previously assumed safe without checking).
  * Verified end-to-end against real running services (not just
    markup review): confirmed a Pi with no reachable backend
    correctly classifies as unavailable via the same health-check
    logic the browser runs, confirmed the drill-down's MJPEG stream
    request returns correct multipart headers, and confirmed the
    bottom-bar Annotate toggle and right-panel OSD toggle both reach
    the real picam-orchestrator backend through the proxy chain.

