picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606220805) stable; urgency=low

  * Sidebar Date/Time now shows the camera feed's embedded timestamp
    (frame_ts_us from /status.json) instead of the viewer's browser
    clock. Anchors to the latest value on each 3s status poll, then
    ticks forward smoothly every second in between using
    performance.now() as a monotonic elapsed-time reference — the
    display updates every second rather than jumping only when a new
    poll lands or freezing in between polls.
  * Verified end-to-end against picam-stream's new frame_ts_us field:
    confirmed the proxied value matches the backend's exactly, and
    that the resulting displayed date reflects the camera feed's time
    rather than today's real date.

