picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606220744) stable; urgency=medium

  * Added an Overlay toggle switch in the sidebar that turns the
    camera-ID/timestamp burn-in on the selected Pi's stream on/off
    instantly, via a new /osd?pi=X&enabled=true|false proxy route.
    Mirrors picam-stream's matching runtime endpoint. The switch
    syncs to the backend's actual reported state on every status
    poll, so it stays accurate if another viewer or a config restart
    changes it elsewhere.
  * Security fix: added sanitizeForRequestLine(), which strips CR/LF
    from any decoded query-param value before it's concatenated into
    an outbound HTTP request line this frontend sends to a backend
    Pi. Without this, a crafted request (e.g. a stream= or enabled=
    value containing percent-encoded CRLF) could have injected
    arbitrary extra header lines into the proxied backend request.
    Applied to both the existing /stream proxy (stream= param) and
    the new /osd proxy (enabled= param). Verified the stripping
    behavior in isolation before shipping.

 -- Jaco Hanekom <jhanekom@gmail.com>  Mon, 22 Jun 2026 07:44:47 +0000

picam-frontend (1.0.0+202606200631) stable; urgency=low

  * Initial release. Single web UI that proxies MJPEG streams and
    status JSON from one or more picam-stream backends, letting a
    browser view and switch between multiple Pis from one page.
  * Pi list is static, configured in [pis] in config.ini.
  * Browsers never connect directly to a Pi — only to this frontend,
    which proxies the actual stream bytes through itself.
  * Fixed a clean-shutdown bug caught during testing: close()ing the
    listening socket does not reliably unblock a thread parked inside
    accept() on that fd. Confirmed via gdb thread dump — the accept
    thread stayed blocked even after close() ran, hanging the
    destructor's join() forever. Fixed with shutdown(fd, SHUT_RDWR)
    before close().

 -- Jaco Hanekom <jhanekom@gmail.com>  Sat, 20 Jun 2026 06:31:51 +0000
